<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In "Keeping Manson Behind Bars" (May 14), Martin Kasindorf wrote: "Outraged 
middle-class values have reasserted themselves, quite literally with a 
vengeance." This statement reveals a lot more about the attitudes of the author 
than it does about society. To attribute outrage over sadistic attacks on 
innocent people to "middle-class values" is to side with the fundamental 
assumptions of the Manson point of view. 
</P>
<P>
Tell me, in which social class in America is sadistic murder regarded as 
acceptable? 
</P>
<P>
LARRY SELK 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
