<P>
IN DEFENSE OF CABO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As frequent visitors to Cabo San Lucas, our experience has been totally 
different from criticism that appeared in your Letters section recently. 
</P>
<P>
Prices are not sky high in most places. We were there in May and had many 
delicious meals for under $10. Cabo is still a place of great natural beauty 
with a superior climate and a picturesque bay, crystal-clear water and clean, 
uncrowded beaches. It's so inviting and romantic that we can't wait for our 
next trip. 
</P>
<P>
HARLEY and KAY PATTISON 
</P>
