<HEADLINE>
<P>
HISTORY LESSONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To set the record straight: The "halcyon days" of Roller Derby (to use the 
quotation that Meyers attributed to Bill Griffiths) occurred when Griffiths was 
50% partner in Roller Derby with Jerry Hill, from 1962 to 1971. Griffiths and 
Hill were both responsible for the success of Roller Derby, along with many 
other talented people. 
</P>
<P>
To imply that Bill Griffiths was singularly responsible for rebuilding Roller 
Derby into a business success that eventually led to RollerGames is both 
inaccurate and unfair to Jerry Hill, my father. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID A. HILL 
</P>
<P>
President, Mediacom Inc. 
</P>
<P>
Ft. Collins, Colo. 
