<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORMER PASADENA MAYOR BOYD WELIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Boyd P. (Bud) Welin, civic activist, former mayor of Pasadena and a lifelong 
supporter of USC, has died at his Laguna Hills home, USC officials announced 
this week. 
</P>
<P>
Welin, who with his late wife established a professorship in pharmaceutical 
sciences at USC in 1988, was 85 when he died June 14. 
</P>
<P>
A pharmacist who graduated from USC in 1927, Welin was a former member of the 
USC Board of Trustees and past president of the General Alumni Assn. He 
co-founded the Brown and Welin Prescription Pharmacists firm in Pasadena after 
Army service in World War II and owned it solely from 1969 to 1979, when he 
sold it. 
</P>
<P>
He was mayor of Pasadena from 1966 until he resigned in 1968, citing the press 
of business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
