<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIRA COSTA HIGH NAMES NEW FOOTBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Larry Petrill, a former assistant coach at El Camino College and San Jose 
State, has been named head football coach at Mira Costa High, the school 
announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Petrill succeeds Dave Brown, who was not rehired by the South Bay Union High 
School District after guiding the Mustangs to a 1-9 record in his one season as 
coach. 
</P>
<P>
Petrill was the defensive coordinator at El Camino under former Coach Jack 
Reilly and was the defensive back coach at San Jose State for three years. He 
has not coached during the last two years. 
</P>
<P>
"We're really thrilled about hiring Larry Petrill," Mira Costa Athletic 
Director Herb Hinsche said. "He's a tremendous coach and a tremendous role 
model for kids." 
</P>
<P>
Hinsche and Petrill were assistant coaches together at Aviation High under Ron 
Veres. 
</P>
<P>
A South Bay native, Petrill attended Morningside High and went on to play 
football at El Camino and USC. He was the Athlete of the Year at El Camino in 
1965 and played nose guard for USC in the 1967 Rose Bowl game. ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
