<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO QUAKES SHAKE TETONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JACKSON, Wyo. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two 4.1- magnitude earthquakes shook residents awake early Saturday, but no 
damage or injuries were reported, officials at the U.S. Geological Survey in 
Golden, Colo., said. The temblors struck five miles north of this community. It 
was not immediately known whether the second quake, occurring an hour later, 
was an aftershock of the first. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
EARTHQUAKES -- WYOMING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA062589-0148 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 74654 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 25, 1989, Sunday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
