<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERU SENTENCES JAPAN SKIPPER IN SUB DEATHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LIMA, Peru 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A court sentenced the captain of a Japanese fishing boat to two years in prison 
for his role in a 1988 collision that sank a Peruvian submarine, killing eight 
sailors, judicial officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the sentence handed to captain Tsukasa Okado, the pilot and 
watchman were sentenced to one year in prison. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Aug. 26 off the Peruvian port of Callao when the Japanese 
boat Kyowa Maru, fishing without authorization in Peruvian territorial waters, 
struck the submarine Pacocha. 
</P>
</TEXT>
