<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANG GETS CENTRE COURT OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WIMBLEDON, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Chang, the Placentia teen-ager who won the French Open only two weeks 
ago, has been rewarded with a Centre Court match when Wimbledon begins Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Chang, who at 17 is the youngest winner of a Grand Slam title, will play Bill 
Scanlon in the third match. 
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Stefan Edberg, beaten by Chang in the French final, plays 
the opening game on Centre Court against Canadian Chris Pridham and will be 
followed by former champion Jimmy Connors against Andrei Cherkasov of the 
Soviet Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
